recordings.loc: OSU's Waterman Farm wood lot, Columbus, Franklin County, Ohio
recordings.rmk:
See XC179676 and XC179679 (XC179681) for a recordings just prior to this one. Recorded along the southeast margin of the wood lot on the Ohio State University experimental farm (Waterman Farm; limited access) located in urban Columbus, OH adjacent to the OSU campus (see map). While recording a Canada Warbler in honey suckle bushes and adjacent lower branches of trees along the edge of the wood lot, a Mourning Warbler appeared lower in the same vegetation and joined the Canada Warbler's late morning singing. This recording was made after the Mourning left the area. All of this session's Mourning Warbler recordings: at the end of XC179676 and throughout XC179679 (XC179681 cropped from XC179679). All of this session's Canada Warbler recordings: XC179676, XC179679 (XC179681 cropped from XC179679), and XC179691. Audacity software was used for post-processing of recordings (signal:noise reduction via high pass filter, then amplification).  

eBird Checklist: <http://ebird.org/ebird/view/checklist?subID=S18532024>

recordings.loc: Oxford, Lafayette County, Mississippi
recordings.rmk:
Natural sound. Bird moving along lower branches of a large Sweet Gum tree near the trunk and and along attached vines approximately 7m above the ground. 

#Habitat#
29-acre estate centrally located in Oxford, MS consisting of antebellum home surrounded by lawns and adjacent forest. Privet hedges and small thickets divide the grounds into distinct lawn units. Bordered on all sides by mature oak-hickory forest. Forest edge consists of oak spp, hickory spp, red cedar, mulberry, with understory along the edge dominated by privet (Ligustrum sp.). Grounds around the house include isolated trees and manicured hedges. A path from the end of the parking area leads northward ~1 km through the forest to the northern edge of the property abutting the University of Mississippi campus

#Editing#
Edited in Adobe Audition. Butterworth high-pass filter, order 3, cutoff frequency 800 Hz

#Equipment#
Fostex FR-2 digital recorder with Sennheiser microphone and Telinga pro 22" parabolic reflector.

recordings.loc: OSU's Waterman Farm wood lot, Columbus, Franklin County, Ohio
recordings.rmk:
Recorded along the southeast margin of the wood lot on the Ohio State University experimental farm (Waterman Farm; limited access) located in urban Columbus, OH adjacent to the OSU campus (see map). The Canada Warbler was first seen and heard along a stream inside the wood lot, then moved to the edge of the wood lot while I ran back to my car to get recording equipment. There, it was mostly in honey suckle bushes or adjacent lower branches of trees along the edge of the wood lot.  I was pleasantly surprised to have a Mourning Warbler do the audio-equivalent of "photo bombing" my Canada Warbler recording!  All of this session's Mourning Warbler recordings: at the end of XC179676 and throughout XC179679 (XC179681 cropped from XC179679). All of this session's Canada Warbler recordings: XC179676, XC179679 (XC179681 cropped from XC179679), and XC179691. Audacity software was used for post-processing of recordings (signal:noise reduction via high pass filter, then amplification).  Eastern Chipmunk also audible in the background. 

eBird Checklist: <http://ebird.org/ebird/view/checklist?subID=S18532024>

recordings.loc: Sucumbíos: Río Coca, Parroquia Simón Bolívar, 1100 m
Carlisle Swamp, Estabrook Woods, Middlesex County, Massachusetts
recordings.rmk: During swamp survey for Canada Warbler territories. This recording is birds 2 and 3 of 3 singing on territory. As I passed through territory of 2nd bird, 3rd was still a hundred yards north, but as I approached its territory, 2nd seems to have followed. Thus, both birds singing singing perhaps only 200 feet apart. After recording I exited the swamp to avoid any further disruption.

recordings.loc: Carlisle Swamp, Estabrook Woods, Middlesex County, Massachusetts
recordings.rmk: During survey for Canada Warbler territories in Carlisle Swamp, Estabrook Woods, Concord, MA, June 22, 2015. CAWA here is one of three, and the southmost individual. Recorded within the swamp, standing in water within dense understory with view only of some sky.

recordings.loc: Brantford, Brant County, Ontario
recordings.rmk: Decent recording but target species is in background. COYE and Black and White Warbler are louder in this recording. Adding to Xeno Canto because ebird flagged as rare. This was recorded by the roadside in a swamp that was mostly deciduous with a few cedar trees. There were two singing. One either side of the road.
